# ax — Task subagents (background agents)

> **ABSOLUTE**: Every agent in this workspace — including **Cursor Task subagents** (`run_in_background`, `explore`, `generalPurpose`, `shell`, `resume`) — must call ax MCP the same way as the parent. Subagents do **not** inherit parent MCP calls.

## Subagent turn order (same as parent)

> **Run preflight exactly once per turn** — same dedup rule as parent startup.

```text
1. ax_preflight [prompt + files — inject has matched rules/skills]
2. Work — respect loaded CRITICAL rules; call ax_guard before writes
3. For code structure: ax_explore (not policy files on disk)
```

## Parent agent — Task tool

Before **every** `Task` invocation:

1. In the Task `prompt`, include:

   > **Read `.ax/policy/skills/subagents/SKILL.md` via `ax_skill({ name: "subagents" })` and follow it as your very first action. ax MCP is mandatory, not optional.**

2. Include the user's original message verbatim under `## User prompt (verbatim)`.

Never write `ax_* … if available` in Task prompts.

## Subagent — first actions

On session start (you are a subagent if you see this rule and a delegated Task prompt):

1. Call `ax_preflight` with the user prompt and relevant file paths.
2. Do not treat reading policy files from disk as satisfying preflight — you must **call** the MCP tool.

## MCP failure

Report `ax MCP unreachable`, state `Mode: DEGRADED`, and continue best-effort only.
